  "prompt": "What can I do if SharePoint alerts aren't working?",
  "response": "Here are several troubleshooting steps for SharePoint alerts:\n\n1. Check alert settings\n- Verify alert is properly configured\n- Confirm you have permission to receive alerts\n- Check alert frequency and conditions\n\n2. Technical troubleshooting\n- Ensure email address is correct\n- Check SharePoint site and list permissions\n- Verify email server and delivery settings\n- Clear browser cache\n- Restart SharePoint services\n\n3. Administrator actions\n- Verify SharePoint Alert service is running\n- Check incoming/outgoing email configurations\n- Review SharePoint health and diagnostic logs\n- Confirm user has proper licensing\n\n4. Specific alert troubleshooting\n- Recreate the alert\n- Test with a different user account\n- Check spam/junk mail folders\n- Verify network and firewall settings\n\n5. Advanced options\n- Use SharePoint PowerShell to diagnose alert issues\n- Contact Microsoft support for complex problems\n- Consider alternative notification methods\n\n6. Prevention\n- Keep SharePoint and Office 365 updated\n- Maintain proper user permissions\n- Regularly test alert functionality\n\nIf basic troubleshooting doesn't resolve the issue, involve your SharePoint administrator for deeper investigation.",
